I have used two P4080DS:

One ethernet port at the top,
4 lower etherent port in a row (counting from left to right)
Old one:
- label with red tape
- using Rev 1 silicon
- running at 1.5 MHz 
- used for Video Benchmarking
- 3rd ethernet connector <--> local switch
- 4th ethernet connector <--> ceiling port
(Drop box: 2.4.484 Green port:
   IP 172.22.12.144 / 255.255.255.128,
   GW 172.22.12.129)

New one:
- label with green tape
- using Rev 2 silicon
- Running at 1.2 MHz
- Used for Linux development
- 3rd ethernet connector <--> local switch
- 4th ethernet connector <--> ceiling port
(Drop box: 2.4.483 Green port:
   IP 172.22.12.143 / 255.255.255.128,
   GW 172.22.12.129)


